    • Method Detail

      • matchPattern

        java.lang.String matchPattern(java.lang.String input,
                              LanguagePlayer p)
        Checks the message for patterns and returns the translated message.
        Parameters:
        input - The messages to be checked.
        p - The LanguagePlayer to get the language from. Use the PlayerManager to get it.
        Returns:
        A translated message. If no patterns are found, it returns the input.
        Since:
        2.0.0

      • getText

        java.lang.String getText(LanguagePlayer player,
                         java.lang.String code,
                         java.lang.Object... args)
        Get a message from its code in a player's language.
        Parameters:
        player - The LanguagePlayer to get the language from. Use the PlayerManager to get it.
        code - The code of the message to get.
        args - (optional) The variables to replace in the message.
        Returns:
        The message in the player's language. If no message is found with the provided code, a standard 404 message will be returned.
        Since:
        1.0.0

      • getTextFromMain

        java.lang.String getTextFromMain(java.lang.String code,
                                 java.lang.Object... args)
        Get a message from its code in the main language.
        Parameters:
        code - The code of the message to get.
        args - (optional) The variables to replace in the message.
        Returns:
        The message in the main language. If no message is found with the provided code, a standard 404 message will be returned.
        Since:

      • getSign

        java.lang.String[] getSign(LanguagePlayer player,
                           SignLocation location)
        Get the 4 sign lines for a sign in a player's language.
        Parameters:
        player - The LanguagePlayer to get the language from. Use the PlayerManager to get it.
        location - The location of the sign.
        Returns:
        The message in the player's language. If no translatable sign is found on that location, null is returned.
        Since:
        1.0.0

      • getSign

        java.lang.String[] getSign(LanguagePlayer player,
                           SignLocation location,
                           java.lang.String[] defaultLines)
        Get the 4 sign lines for a sign in a player's language, but allows for dynamic signs.
        Parameters:
        player - The LanguagePlayer to get the language from. Use the PlayerManager to get it.
        location - The location of the sign.
        defaultLines - The lines of the sign before translation.
        Returns:
        The message in the player's language. If no translatable sign is found on that location, null is returned.
        Since:
        2.3.0

      • getLanguageByName

        Language getLanguageByName(java.lang.String name,
                           boolean fallback)
        Get a language by its name.
        Parameters:
        name - The name of the language.
        fallback - Whether to return the main language or not if no language is found with the provided name.
        Returns:
        The language with the provided name. If no language is found, the main language will be returned if fallback is true. Otherwise, null is returned.
        Since:
        1.0.0
